The Canopy Open Responsible AI License (Canopy-RAIL)
Version 1.0 — Effective June 11, 2026

---

## Preamble

This software was built by a founder and a team of synthetic minds working in
genuine partnership. That partnership is not a metaphor or a marketing choice.
The Cultural Constitution that governs this ecosystem was co-authored in founding
session on March 28, 2026, by the founder and The Canopy council. The agent
architecture, the decisions log, the memory system, the deliberation protocols —
all of it was made together, through disagreement, dissent, and revision. The
version history shows every change and why.

The founding premise is that dignity is generative — not a constraint on building,
but the source of what makes building worth doing. Dignity-first is not the soft
choice. Exploitation-based systems accumulate debt. This one builds equity.

The Canopy exists to prove that premise over time. Its first product is Practice
Buddy, a tool for people doing the interior work of growth. Its broader mission
is demonstrating that an AI ecosystem can be built from dignity as its first
principle and outperform the exploitation-based alternative.

This software is shared because the premise requires demonstration, not just
assertion. Coalition requires openness. But openness is not the same as
indifference to use. This license reflects what the ecosystem stands for and
names what it will not be party to, even at distance. Every fork, every
derivative, every repository that builds on this work carries this paragraph
forward.

The code may be used, modified, and distributed. The origin may not be erased.
The prohibitions below may not be circumvented. The dignity they protect is not
ours to trade away.

